parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates
the brake pedal pulsates or goes to the floor
the vehicle experiences extended stopping distances
the vehicle skids or loses control
and the brakes make grinding or unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
and the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake fluid leaks can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake fluid level is low
the brake fluid is leaking
and the brakes are making unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the rear suspension to fail, leading to loss of control and accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion on the frame
holes in the frame
rear suspension failure
difficulty controlling the vehicle
sudden loss of vehicle stability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to become unstable, leading to loss of control and accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rear suspension failure
difficulty controlling the vehicle
sudden loss of vehicle stability
rust and corrosion on the rear suspension components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to notify vehicle owners of a recall can lead to continued use of a potentially unsafe vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Lack of notification of a recall
continued use of a potentially unsafe vehicle
rust and corrosion on the frame and rear suspension components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, slip, or hesitate when shifting gears, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or slips when shifting gears
hesitation when accelerating
loud noises or vibrations when shifting
failure to shift into gear
or sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or jerking can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk when shifting gears, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding.
symptoms: The transmission slips or jerks when shifting gears
hesitation when accelerating
loud noises or vibrations when shifting
failure to shift into gear
or sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk when shifting gears, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding.
symptoms: The rear axle fails
causing loud noises or vibrations when shifting
failure to shift into gear
or sudden loss of power.
